“[Notre Dame is] an architectural jewel of a collective memory,” he said, noting its significance to Catholics around the world.
A disclaimer stating “this post is not about the fire at Notre Dame” was only available after users clicked through the link to the story.
Other Islamophobes began widely circulating a video of the fire at Notre Dame overlaid with unrelated audio of people shouting “Allahu Akbar,” before YouTube, Twitter, and other platforms removed it from their platforms.
Key to each of those examples is the idea that “western civilization,” represented by the iconic Notre Dame, is under attack from non-“western” individuals or forces and echoes many conspiracies propagated by white nationalists.
The racist and Islamophobic discourse surrounding the far-right’s discussion of Notre Dame, he said, misses the point.